paragraphs.name: 077e
paragraphs.text: You have to care about legacy more than ego.

paragraphs.name: 7fca
paragraphs.text: This doesn’t mean you have to be a jack of all trades, but you must become a master of some. For example, all the professional writers I know are good at more than one thing. One is a great publicist. Another is really smart at leadership. Another is a fantastic speaker.
2. Amateurs want to arrive. Pros want to get better.
paragraphs.name: 833c
55b5
paragraphs.text: You have to know what you are before you can figure out what you want to do.

paragraphs.name: 003f
paragraphs.text: You have to practice even, maybe especially, when it hurts.

paragraphs.name: 1ccd
paragraphs.text: I recently spoke with a best-selling author who has sold tens of millions of books. Do you know when his career started to really take off? It was when he wrote his 125th book at age 45.

In my case, I spent too long waiting for someone to call me a writer before I was willing to act like one. Now I’ve learned that clarity comes with action. We must perform our way into professionalism. We must first call ourselves what we want to become, and then get to the work of mastery.
paragraphs.name: f5f8

paragraphs.text: I recently spoke with a creative professional in New York who makes a living as both a fine artist and a photographer. He knows, as all professionals do,that all our skills complement each other and, frankly, relieve us from putting too much pressure on ourselves to be the world’s best at any one thing.
paragraphs.name: 4b0c

paragraphs.text: If you don’t do this, you delude yourself into thinking you’re better than you really are, which is the fastest route to failure and anonymity.
paragraphs.name: 70c7

paragraphs.text: This doesn’t mean you have to be a jack of all trades, but you must become a master of some. For example, all the professional writers I know are good at more than one thing. One is a great publicist. Another is really smart at leadership. Another is a fantastic speaker.
paragraphs.name: 7fca
94cd
paragraphs.text: Turns out, I was still acting the amateur, thinking success as a writer was about finding the right idea or a big break. But the truth is that success in any field is more about commitment to a process than it is about finding one magic trick that will make it all come together.

paragraphs.name: 73f4
paragraphs.text: Either way, you must develop your own portfolio.

paragraphs.name: f48b
paragraphs.text: You have to become a student long before you get to be a master.

paragraphs.name: 90e8
paragraphs.text: If you want to be a pro in your field, you’re going to have to break this terrible amateur habit of looking at what people have without paying attention to what they did to get it. Chasing the results without understanding the process will lead to short-lived success, if not outright failure.

paragraphs.text: Amazing how many scumbags you’ve used as shining examples to prove your point. Thomas Edison was a thief of the worst order, and John Grisham hasn’t written a book in over a decade despite the number of titles published in his name. That’s a theft of the reader’s trust, even if it’s legal.

content.subtitle: But my experiences as a teacher breathe life into my stories. I no longer take the time I have to write for granted.

paragraphs.name: 98c9
paragraphs.text: This is so true. When I left my job as a journalist to become a teacher, I figured my writing would suffer. I was able to write four to five hours most days as a reporter. I now log about an hour each day.
But my experiences as a teacher breathe life into my stories. I no longer take the time I have to write for granted.
